<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="../../w/index-title=History_of_timekeeping_devices&action=edit&section=24.php.html" title="Edit section: Footnotes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Footnotes">Footnotes</span></h2>
<div class="reflist references-column-width" style="-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-David_Landes_18f.-1"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-David_Landes_18f._1-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">David Landes: "Revolution in Time: Clocks and the Making of the Modern World", rev. and enlarged edition, Harvard University Press, Cambridge 2000, <a href="Special_BookSources/0674002822" class="internal mw-magiclink-isbn">ISBN 0-674-00282-2</a>, p.18f.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-2"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#CITEREFLewis2000">Lewis 2000</a>, pp.&#160;356f.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-needham_411-3"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-needham_411_3-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-needham_411_3-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation Journal" id="CITEREFNeedham1986"><a href="Joseph_Needham" title="Joseph Needham">Needham, Joseph</a> (1986). "Science and Civilization in China". <i>Physics and Physical Technology, Part 2: Mechanical Engineering</i> (Taipei: Caves Books, Ltd) <b>4</b>: 411.</span></span></li>
